{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-blogs-blog-detail-js","path":"/blog/kick-starting-with-progressive-web-apps-part-5","result":{"pageContext":{"post":{"id":"1b3851a9-426f-55c1-abe9-55530ebc6406","title":"Kick starting with Progressive Web Apps Part 5","excerpt":"Till now our site is ready to work offline!","_rawBody":[{"_key":"a65176ab0975","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"a65176ab09750","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Till now our site is ready to work offline!"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"bd9231b24efc","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"bd9231b24efc0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Further you can also notify users whether they are offline or online by adding event listeners of online/offline events. These two events are fired on each page when the browser switches between online and offline mode."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"919ada810550","_type":"code","code":"//index.html \r\n<script>\r\nwindow.addEventListener('load', function() {\r\n   function network_status(event) {\r\n       if (navigator.onLine) {\r\n          console.log(\"You are online!\");\r\n          var e = document.getElementById(\"snackbar\");\r\n          e.innerHTML = \"You are online!\";\r\n          e.className = \"show\", setTimeout(function() {\r\n          e.className = e.className.replace(\"show\", \"\")\r\n          }, 1500)\r\n       }\r\n       else\r\n       {\r\n         console.log(\"You are offline!\");\r\n         var e = document.getElementById(\"snackbar\");\r\n         e.innerHTML = \"You are offline!\";\r\n         e.className = \"show\", setTimeout(function() {\r\n         e.className = e.className.replace(\"show\", \"\")\r\n         }, 1500)\r\n       }\r\n   }\r\nwindow.addEventListener('online', network_status);\r\nwindow.addEventListener('offline', network_status);\r\nnetwork_status();\r\n});\r\n</script>"},{"_key":"48b84b095e1e","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"48b84b095e1e0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Also add an element tag in index.html showing the message as ‘You are offline!’ when there is no Internet connectivity."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"803fcb24196a","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"803fcb24196a0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"You can use snackbar for displaying the message. If you are unaware about snackbar have a look at below :"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"2db629985592","_type":"urllink","shortDescription":"Well organized and easy to understand Web building tutorials with lots of examples of how to use HTML, CSS, JavaScript… ","title":"How To Create a Snackbar / Toast ","urlLink":"https://www.w3schools.com/howto/howto_js_snackbar.asp"},{"_key":"04ff120dcbb7","_type":"code","code":"//index.html (inside body tag)\r\n<div id=\"snackbar\" class=\"hide\">You are Offline!</div>"},{"_key":"aa573473c584","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"aa573473c5840","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Implement "},{"_key":"aa573473c5841","_type":"span","marks":["strong"],"text":"Gray scale filter"},{"_key":"aa573473c5842","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" over the things when the user is offline by adding CSS to the page."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"a1f203f87379","_type":"code","code":"//css (add a class of gray filter to css)\r\n.is-offline {\r\n   filter: grayscale(1);\r\n   cursor: default;\r\n }\r\n//index.html\r\n<script>\r\nwindow.addEventListener('load', function() {\r\n   function network_status(event) {\r\n       if (navigator.onLine) {\r\n          console.log(\"You are online!\");\r\n          document.documentElement.classList.remove(\"is-offline\");\r\n          var e = document.getElementById(\"snackbar\");\r\n          e.innerHTML = \"You are online!\";\r\n          e.className = \"show\", setTimeout(function() {\r\n          e.className = e.className.replace(\"show\", \"\")\r\n          }, 1500)\r\n       }\r\n       else\r\n       {\r\n         console.log(\"You are offline!\");\r\n         document.documentElement.classList.add(\"is-offline\");\r\n         var e = document.getElementById(\"snackbar\");\r\n         e.innerHTML = \"You are offline!\";\r\n         e.className = \"show\", setTimeout(function() {\r\n         e.className = e.className.replace(\"show\", \"\")\r\n         }, 1500)\r\n       }\r\n   }\r\nwindow.addEventListener('online', network_status);\r\nwindow.addEventListener('offline', network_status);\r\nnetwork_status();\r\n});\r\n</script>"},{"_key":"b74fd16d8227","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"b74fd16d82270","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"That’s it! You have your installable web app just like a native app which can now work even Offline."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"64187a94cc52","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"64187a94cc520","_type":"span","marks":["strong"],"text":"To kick start with Progressive Web App you can go through my blogs :"},{"_key":"64187a94cc521","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"\n\n1) "},{"_key":"64187a94cc522","_type":"span","marks":["94b5e011ce48"],"text":"Register service worker and cache the resources in our app on the initial load."},{"_key":"64187a94cc523","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"\n\n2) "},{"_key":"64187a94cc524","_type":"span","marks":["99f08603cbb4"],"text":"Update the old service worker and cache the new response in Cache Storage."},{"_key":"64187a94cc525","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"\n\n3) "},{"_key":"64187a94cc526","_type":"span","marks":["46b5de8d3885"],"text":"Get out the resources from the cache and intercept the network requests."},{"_key":"64187a94cc527","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"\n\n4) "},{"_key":"64187a94cc528","_type":"span","marks":["bf8b25974456"],"text":"Make our web app installable via the Web App Manifest File."},{"_key":"64187a94cc529","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"\n\n5) Grey out the things when offline."}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"94b5e011ce48","_type":"link","href":"https://medium.com/@shailajashah93/kick-starting-with-progressive-web-apps-part-1-6701c9ea348"},{"_key":"99f08603cbb4","_type":"link","href":"https://medium.com/@shailajashah93/kick-starting-with-progressive-web-apps-part-2-99c3dd969446"},{"_key":"46b5de8d3885","_type":"link","href":"https://medium.com/@shailajashah93/kick-starting-with-progressive-web-apps-part-3-4d3f139f6f07"},{"_key":"bf8b25974456","_type":"link","href":"https://medium.com/@shailajashah93/kick-starting-with-progressive-web-apps-part-4-cd901de01a82"}],"style":"blockquote"},{"Separatorr":true,"_key":"99dabace9c38","_type":"separator"},{"_key":"c512b6ed5ab9","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"c512b6ed5ab90","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":""},{"_key":"c512b6ed5ab91","_type":"span","marks":["de97a146f8f9"],"text":"SoluteLabs"},{"_key":"c512b6ed5ab92","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" is a high-performance team of 25 focused on mobile and web design and development; we have produced top #10 chart topping applications on Android and iOS app stores, graphics that have gone viral and applications with Millions of downloads."}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"de97a146f8f9","_type":"link","href":"https://www.solutelabs.com/"}],"style":"normal"}],"_rawFaq":null,"publishedAt":"2017-03-28T18:30:00.000Z","_updatedAt":"2020-08-31T08:30:32Z","readingTime":"2 min read","altTagMainImage":null,"titleMetaData":null,"shortanchorlinkh2":[],"categories":[{"id":"61b2fbb3-23c5-54d6-aac3-bf8ba2dcecc3","title":"Blog"}],"mainImage":{"asset":{"id":"image-ae8118de3f070633484686f7a8251dbaf023c205-2240x1260-png","url":"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/ay6gmb6r/production/ae8118de3f070633484686f7a8251dbaf023c205-2240x1260.png","fluid":{"sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px","src":"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/ay6gmb6r/production/ae8118de3f070633484686f7a8251dbaf023c205-2240x1260.png?w=800&h=450&fit=crop","srcSet":"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/ay6gmb6r/production/ae8118de3f070633484686f7a8251dbaf023c205-2240x1260.png?w=200&h=113&fit=crop 200w,\nhttps://cdn.sanity.io/images/ay6gmb6r/production/ae8118de3f070633484686f7a